Data on this page are extracted at 3pm on weekdays and loaded to the page at 4pm the same day (except on statutory holidays). iPHIS is a dynamic disease reporting system that allow for ongoing updates; data represent a snapshot at the time of extraction and may differ from previous or subsequent dashboard updates. Data are presented for ongoing and recently closed (past 14 days) confirmed reportable outbreaks in institutional settings, congregate settings, childcare and schools.


Provincial respiratory outbreak definitions are available here: https://www.health.gov.on.ca/en/pro/programs/publichealth/oph_standards/docs/respiratory_outbreaks_chapter.pdf


Details on respiratory virus testing in Ontario are available here:

https://www.publichealthontario.ca/en/Laboratory-Services/Test-Information-Index/Virus-Respiratory

Data notes

The total number of ongoing outbreaks in the overall summary will not match the total of Table 1's columns if there are outbreaks with co-infections (e.g., influenza and another respiratory virus). Co-infection outbreaks will appear in multiple columns.


As of November 14, 2022, all symptomatic individuals in healthcare institutions (long-term care homes, retirement homes, public hospitals) may be tested for SARS-CoV-2, influenza and RSV, while only the first 4 symptomatic individuals are tested for other respiratory viruses (e.g. parainfluenza). Subsequent symptomatic individuals are counted as cases if they have a common epidemiological link (e.g. same unit, same floor).
